# Release artifact — TRACKED, not ignored (org rule 6: releases = annotated
# tags + committed artifacts). `make vsix`/`make release` always produce a
# deterministic `<name>-<version>.vsix` filename, so there is no separate
# "dev build" name to exclude by pattern. Every package is source-map-free
# (package.json's `vscode:prepublish` forces the release bundle before any
# `vsce package`); the discipline is procedural, not path-based — only
# commit a .vsix that came from a green `make release` (clean floor + full
# gate + vsix-verify), not an ad-hoc `make vsix` run mid-edit.
